e. Step through, and a small entryway leads to a stairwell that rises into the main living area, a series of compact, carefully composed spaces.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-stairs-030625-1151-08.jpg 1652w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-stairs-030625-1151-08-940x1457.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-stairs-030625-1151-08-800x1240.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-stairs-030625-1151-08-768x1190.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-stairs-030625-1151-08-991x1536.jpg 991w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-stairs-030625-1151-08-1322x2048.jpg 1322w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1652px) 100vw, 1652px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe dining area features a round wooden table with two chairs, framed by soft light that spills in from multiple angles. Just beyond, the kitchen balances subtlety with surprise: light grey minimalist cabinetry, matte black hardware, and a backsplash of glazed purple subway tiles that shimmer like amethyst.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1470\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-09.jpg\" alt=\"The dining area of this modern laneway house features a round wooden table with two chairs, framed by soft light that spills in from multiple angles. Just beyond, the kitchen balances subtlety with surprise: light grey minimalist cabinetry, matte black hardware, and a backsplash of glazed purple subway tiles that shimmer like amethyst.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-09.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-09-940x720.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-09-800x613.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-09-768x588.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-09-1536x1176.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1438\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10.jpg\" alt=\"The dining area of this modern laneway house features a round wooden table with two chairs, framed by soft light that spills in from multiple angles.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10.jpg 1438w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10-940x1673.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10-800x1424.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10-768x1367.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10-863x1536.jpg 863w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-dining-kitchen-030625-1151-10-1150x2048.jpg 1150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1438px) 100vw, 1438px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWood floors run throughout the home, grounding each space with natural warmth. In the living area, a small grey couch is dressed with turquoise accent pillows. Above it, a narrow horizontal window lets in gentle daylight, while a pair of floating white shelves display personal objects and art. A tall vertical window beside the bedroom door adds a bright moment to the transition between spaces.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1765\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11.jpg\" alt=\"Wood floors run throughout this laneway home, grounding each space with natural warmth. In the living area, a small grey couch is dressed with turquoise accent pillows. Above it, a narrow horizontal window lets in gentle daylight, while a pair of floating white shelves display personal objects and art. A tall vertical window beside the bedroom door adds a bright moment to the transition between spaces.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11.jpg 1765w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11-940x1363.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11-800x1160.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11-768x1114.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11-1059x1536.jpg 1059w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-living-room-030625-1151-11-1412x2048.jpg 1412w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1765px) 100vw, 1765px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the bedroom, walls in deep blue contrast with a white sloped ceiling, creating a serene cocoon under the canopy of the house. A horizontal window and a skylight above the bed bring the sky into view, while a built-in closet maximizes storage.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1366\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bedroom-030625-1151-12.jpg\" alt=\"In this bedroom, walls in deep blue contrast with a white sloped ceiling, creating a serene cocoon under the canopy of the house. A horizontal window and a skylight above the bed bring the sky into view, while a built-in closet maximizes storage.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bedroom-030625-1151-12.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bedroom-030625-1151-12-940x669.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bedroom-030625-1151-12-800x569.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bedroom-030625-1151-12-768x546.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bedroom-030625-1151-12-1536x1093.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe bathroom is compact but full of texture. A round vessel sink rests on a drawer-fronted vanity, paired with matte black fixtures and a rounded rectangle mirror. The shower enclosure is lined with wavy tiles, and both the shower floor and bathroom floor sparkle with small, gem-like penny tiles that catch the light and add a touch of quiet glamour.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1887\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13.jpg\" alt=\"This bathroom is compact but full of texture. A round vessel sink rests on a drawer-fronted vanity, paired with matte black fixtures and a rounded rectangle mirror. The shower enclosure is lined with wavy tiles, and both the shower floor and bathroom floor sparkle with small, gem-like penny tiles that catch the light and add a touch of quiet glamour.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13.jpg 1887w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13-940x1275.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13-800x1085.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13-768x1042.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13-1132x1536.jpg 1132w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-bathroom-030625-1151-13-1510x2048.jpg 1510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1887px) 100vw, 1887px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHere’s a look at the architectural drawings that shaped this elevated, tree-conscious home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14.jpg\" alt=\"A compact laneway house rises above a carport to preserve a mature maple tree, blending retro-futuristic form with thoughtful interior design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14-940x940.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14-800x800.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14-200x200.jpg 200w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14-768x768.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-14-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1703\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-15.jpg\" alt=\"A compact laneway house rises above a carport to preserve a mature maple tree, blending retro-futuristic form with thoughtful interior design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-15.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-15-940x834.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-15-800x710.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-15-768x681.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-15-1536x1362.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1224\" height=\"834\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-16.jpg\" alt=\"A compact laneway house rises above a carport to preserve a mature maple tree, blending retro-futuristic form with thoughtful interior design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-16.jpg 1224w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-16-940x640.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-16-800x545.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/modern-laneway-house-architectural-drawings-1151-16-768x523.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1224px) 100vw, 1224px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eNestled in the city yet suspended just above its surface, Pocket Laneway House captures a compelling tension between groundedness and lift-off. It’s a home that honors its context while imagining other worlds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography: Exterior – \u003ca href=\"http://www.birdhousemedia.ca/\"\u003eBirdhouse Media\u003c/a\u003e, Interior – \u003ca href=\"https://davidwhittakerphotographer.com/\"\u003eDavid Whittaker\u003c/a\u003e | Architect: Weiss Architecture \u0026amp; Urbanism Limited – Kevin Weiss, Principal | Engineer: Enrique Tabak | Contractor: Carmelin Design + Build\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
